Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.04,0:00:16.50,B2,YUZU,0000,0000,0000,,Rise and shine, Big Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.35,0:00:22.00,B2,YUZU,0000,0000,0000,,Get up!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.18,0:00:24.52,OS,CAPTION,0000,0000,0000,,ICHIGO KUROSAKI: 17 YEARS OLD
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.15,0:00:30.48,OS,CAPTION,0000,0000,0000,,HAIR COLOR: ORANGE
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.03,0:00:38.45,OS,CAPTION,0000,0000,0000,,EYE COLOR: BROWN
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.70,0:00:42.16,OS,CAPTION,0000,0000,0000,,OCCUPATION:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.31,0:00:44.51,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Still sleepy…
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.75,0:00:48.17,OS,CAPTION,0000,0000,0000,,HIGH SCHOOL STUDENT
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.59,0:00:52.51,OS,CAPTION,0000,0000,0000,,HE CANNOT SEE GHOSTS
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.47,0:02:29.84,B2,YUZU,0000,0000,0000,,Ta-da!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.88,0:02:35.82,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yeah, today’s your \Nschool entrance ceremony.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.77,0:02:40.76,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Karin, pass the soy sauce.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.92,0:02:44.68,B2,YUZU,0000,0000,0000,,Here’s your soy sauce!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.39,0:02:49.10,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,What’re you so angry about, Yuzu?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.31,0:02:51.00,B2,YUZU,0000,0000,0000,,I’m not angry!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.53,0:02:53.51,B2,YUZU,0000,0000,0000,,I saved showing you how I look
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.51,0:02:57.48,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,in my uniform until the day \Nof my entrance ceremony,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.48,0:02:59.62,B2,YUZU,0000,0000,0000,,but you won’t even look at me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.62,0:03:00.57,B2,YUZU,0000,0000,0000,,See if I care!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.34,0:03:03.99,B2,YUZU,0000,0000,0000,,I’m not serving you the tastiest \Nscorched portion of the rice!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.35,0:03:07.93,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Your skirt’s unzipped.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.23,0:03:10.85,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,See? I am looking.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.85,0:03:12.79,B2,YUZU,0000,0000,0000,,Dummy! You’re so dirty-minded!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.63,0:03:19.30,B2,BESPECTACLED GHOST,0000,0000,0000,,My glasses!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.25,0:03:21.80,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,What’s the matter, Karin?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.49,0:03:23.63,B2,KARIN,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.12,0:03:25.47,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,Yuzu!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.84,0:03:27.98,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,Check this out, Yuzu!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.98,0:03:29.48,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,How’s this suit look?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.48,0:03:32.44,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,Which matches better, this \Nnecktie or this bowtie?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.54,0:03:36.25,B2,YUZU,0000,0000,0000,,They both look okay. Doesn’t matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.25,0:03:37.40,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn’t matter?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.86,0:03:38.97,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,Yuzu!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.97,0:03:40.39,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t be like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.39,0:03:42.91,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, take a good look!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.91,0:03:45.91,B2,YUZU,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that’s fine. Whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.32,0:03:47.73,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.56,0:03:49.74,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.68,0:03:58.05,B2,ICHIGO (N),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It’s been 17 months—a little \Nover a year—since that battle…{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.21,0:04:00.86,B2,ICHIGO (N),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I’m in my last year of high school.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.06,0:04:05.06,B2,ICHIGO (N),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Chad and Inoue apparently told{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.06,0:04:07.88,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}everyone about my Soul Reaper powers.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.65,0:04:12.78,B2,ICHIGO (N),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}They said everyone \Nbelieved them right away.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.87,0:04:43.05,B2,ICHIGO (N),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Seeing stuff like that happen \Nright before your eyes{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.05,0:04:45.46,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}doesn’t leave much \Ndoubt, though, you know.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.25,0:04:52.98,B2,ICHIGO (N),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Despite that, everyone \Naccepted me without a word…{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.98,0:04:54.27,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}that was cool.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.87,0:04:55.94,B2,MIZUIRO,0000,0000,0000,,‘Morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.14,0:04:57.90,B2,ICHIGO (N),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But now,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.50,0:05:01.57,B2,ICHIGO (N),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I no longer possess Soul Reaper powers.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.38,0:05:04.66,B2,ICHIGO (N),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ever since I lost my Spirit Energy,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.66,0:05:06.93,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Karin’s own Spirit \NEnergy became stronger…{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.93,0:05:09.53,B2,YUZU,0000,0000,0000,,Have a good day, Big Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.80,0:05:11.90,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I will. You take care, okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.71,0:05:15.60,B2,ICHIGO (N),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Nowadays, the high-level \Nspirit medium abilities{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.60,0:05:16.80,B2,ICHIGO (N),0000,0000,0000,,-{\i1}belong to Karin.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.60,0:05:17.50,B2,YUZU,0000,0000,0000,,-See you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.07,0:05:19.74,B2,ICHIGO (N),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}She’s not too thrilled about it,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.74,0:05:21.71,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,-{\i1}but she doesn’t come \Nto me for advice.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.21,0:05:21.71,B2,YUZU,0000,0000,0000,,-Hey, wait up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.68,0:05:25.38,B2,ICHIGO (N),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Seems like she’s working \Nher way through it okay.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.39,0:05:28.03,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Let’s go, Mizuiro!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.03,0:05:28.95,B2,MIZUIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.27,0:05:35.89,B2,KEIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.33,0:05:38.06,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,What’s up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.02,0:05:42.98,B2,MIZUIRO,0000,0000,0000,,I’ll see you guys later.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.46,0:05:46.47,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. See you at lunch!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.47,0:05:47.79,B2,KEIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo! Ichigo!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.79,0:05:50.45,B2,KEIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I’m tapping! I’m tapping out!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.11,0:05:53.10,B2,TATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,‘Morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.10,0:05:53.70,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.97,0:05:56.48,B2,TATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo, did you bring \Nthe game I lent you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.84,0:06:00.21,B2,TATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,The new one’s coming out \Nsoon, so I need it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.52,0:06:03.09,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I have it right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.62,0:06:10.88,B2,TATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,What? You forgot it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.21,0:06:13.66,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up. I brought it with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.66,0:06:14.35,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.42,0:06:18.56,B2,ICHIGO (N),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Since losing my Soul Reaper powers,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.86,0:06:24.39,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the Combat Pass appears to have \Nceased functioning, as well.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.53,0:06:27.83,B2,ICHIGO (N),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The visual barrier’s gone, and \Nthe Hollow alarm won’t sound.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.83,0:06:29.89,B2,ICHIGO (N),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It’s become a mere piece of wood—{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.89,0:06:32.06,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I even forgot I had put \Nit in my school bag.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.80,0:06:38.21,B2,ICHIGO (N),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now, the only thing left to show \Nthat I was once a Soul Reaper{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.52,0:06:41.10,B2,ICHIGO (N),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}is this thing in my hand.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.22,0:06:46.05,B2,TEACHER IN NEXT CLASS,0000,0000,0000,,Ishida! Where do you \Nthink you’re going?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.38,0:06:47.72,B2,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,To the nurse’s office!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.54,0:06:55.31,B2,ICHIGO (N),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now Ishida is eliminating the \NHollows that I used handle.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.35,0:07:01.29,B2,ICHIGO (N),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You’d think he could \Njust let Imoyama do it,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.85,0:07:04.82,B2,ICHIGO (N),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but the guy seems even less \Ncapable than we thought.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.19,0:07:10.88,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I hope he doesn’t overdo things \Nand upset the Soul Society…{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.34,0:07:14.91,B2,ICHIGO (N),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ever since that day,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.80,0:07:24.00,B2,ICHIGO (N),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Rukia hasn’t been back \Nto Karakura Town even once.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.07,0:07:32.80,B2,KEIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Any plans on what to do for your future?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.36,0:07:37.07,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,You mean like after high school?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.07,0:07:40.43,B2,KEIGO,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean “like”?! \NWhat else is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.16,0:07:43.74,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,We still have time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.43,0:07:46.57,B2,KEIGO,0000,0000,0000,,After this semester, we \Nhave career counseling.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.06,0:07:49.26,B2,KEIGO,0000,0000,0000,,It’s time you start thinking about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.46,0:07:53.90,B2,KEIGO,0000,0000,0000,,You had good grades at the start,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.90,0:07:56.87,B2,KEIGO,0000,0000,0000,,but your grades fell from the second \Nhalf of your first school year…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.87,0:07:58.31,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Quit reminding me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.31,0:08:00.29,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I had a lot going on back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.29,0:08:01.42,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,It couldn’t be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.30,0:08:04.64,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I’m still above average.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.92,0:08:11.61,B2,KEIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder how Rukia is doing these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.87,0:08:15.01,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Why’re you bringing up Rukia now?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.53,0:08:17.06,B2,KEIGO,0000,0000,0000,,You know…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.06,0:08:19.97,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,because I think she could \Nat least drop by sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.41,0:08:23.42,B2,KEIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Since then, she hasn’t \Ndropped by even once.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.42,0:08:24.71,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t you think that’s cold?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.13,0:08:26.41,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,She’s not being cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.96,0:08:29.94,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,She was relieved of her \NKarakura Town duties.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.83,0:08:33.26,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Not coming back is normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.38,0:08:36.62,B2,KEIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t you miss her?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.30,0:08:40.08,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.47,0:08:44.96,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,It took me 16 years to \Nearn this normal life.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.42,0:08:48.21,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I hope it stays peaceful \Nlike this until I die.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.58,0:08:51.88,B2,KEIGO,0000,0000,0000,,You have a good point…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.35,0:08:55.63,B2,KEIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I don’t ever want to go through \Nscary stuff like that again, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.21,0:09:00.10,B2,ICHIGO (N),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That’s right.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.96,0:09:05.02,B2,ICHIGO (N),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I never once felt superior \Nbecause I could see ghosts.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.34,0:09:11.73,B2,ICHIGO (N),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I never thought of making a living \Nfrom it or using it to help others.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.00,0:09:16.32,B2,ICHIGO (N),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All I ever yearned for was a \Nlife without seeing ghosts.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.37,0:09:20.78,B2,ICHIGO (N),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I got the life I yearned for.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.59,0:09:32.38,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Damn it you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.86,0:09:37.08,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.08,0:09:38.66,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Give me back my bag!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.48,0:09:40.49,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Mizuiro.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.18,0:09:42.10,B2,ICHIGO (N),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Come to think of it…{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.73,0:09:43.59,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Hold this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.34,0:09:46.23,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.76,0:09:49.69,B2,ICHIGO (N),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There’s one other thing I still have{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.39,0:09:52.51,B2,ICHIGO (N),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}that proves I was once a Soul Reaper.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.28,0:10:10.54,B2,ICHIGO (N),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The physical training I did and the \Nreflexes I developed in order to win{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.54,0:10:12.50,B2,ICHIGO (N),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}come in handy sometimes.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.50,0:10:13.93,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.15,0:10:16.22,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,That was pretty awesome, kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.65,0:10:17.65,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.02,0:10:19.18,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,You hungry?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.97,0:10:22.57,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,I’ll buy you ramen. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.95,0:10:24.18,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,No thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.32,0:10:27.10,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I want to avoid getting \Nscolded afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.65,0:10:30.81,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Please don’t tell anyone \Nthat I hit somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.10,0:10:32.61,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Sure…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.23,0:10:35.53,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,I see…too bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.26,0:10:38.56,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Let’s go, Mizuiro, Keigo.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.86,0:10:45.73,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Well, what do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.50,0:10:48.77,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,You’re rather cautious…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.01,0:10:57.80,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo Kurosaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.67,0:11:15.65,B2,RENJI/SILHOUETTE,0000,0000,0000,,How long do you plan \Non sleeping, Ichigo?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.65,0:11:17.69,B2,RENJI/SILHOUETTE,0000,0000,0000,,Do I have to slug you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.78,0:11:22.01,B2,BYAKUYA/SILHOUETTE,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, wake up, Ichigo Kurosaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.98,0:11:25.48,B2,RUKIA/SILHOUETTE,0000,0000,0000,,You fool! Get up, Ichigo!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.50,0:11:27.83,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,Get up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.16,0:11:30.22,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,I-chi-go…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.33,0:11:35.56,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.56,0:11:36.78,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,You really are an idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.78,0:11:38.92,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,I could’ve fallen!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.24,0:11:40.62,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,You could’ve killed me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.11,0:11:42.13,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.59,0:11:44.93,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,If you die, you’ll go to \Nthe Soul Society, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.02,0:11:50.10,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,Talking big now, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.38,0:11:53.89,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Look, you’re not going to die \Nfalling from the second floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.54,0:11:56.65,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Because of you, I had a weird dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.65,0:11:59.06,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,To apologize, hurry up and fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.15,0:12:01.56,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,Stop that! I’ll fall!!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.56,0:12:02.53,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,You’re going to make \Nme fall for real!!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.90,0:12:06.49,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,A weird dream? What about?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.90,0:12:12.25,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I don’t remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.87,0:12:15.42,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Trying to tell you made me forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.41,0:12:21.26,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,So what’s your offer?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.78,0:12:24.26,B2,JUDO TEAM MEMBER,0000,0000,0000,,F-Five thousand yen…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.44,0:12:27.31,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Five thousand yen per week?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.67,0:12:28.93,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Get real!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.93,0:12:29.89,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Next!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.18,0:12:31.15,B2,SATODA,0000,0000,0000,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.15,0:12:33.39,B2,SATODA,0000,0000,0000,,I’m Satoda, vice-captain \Nof the soccer team!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.67,0:12:35.87,B2,SATODA,0000,0000,0000,,We’d like to borrow your \Nskills, Mr. Kurosaki…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.87,0:12:37.90,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Just say how long and how much.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.16,0:12:41.85,B2,SATODA,0000,0000,0000,,-We soccer team have prepared \Na budget of two…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.63,0:12:40.72,B2,MIZUIRO,0000,0000,0000,,-Ichigo…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.72,0:12:41.44,B2,MIZUIRO,0000,0000,0000,,-Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.65,0:12:43.18,B2,KEIGO,0000,0000,0000,,-He’s talking business.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.85,0:12:46.16,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,-no, 1.5 times that of the basketball \Nteam you helped out last time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.52,0:12:45.10,B2,KEIGO,0000,0000,0000,,-He’ll be a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.10,0:12:46.40,B2,MIZUIRO,0000,0000,0000,,-Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.16,0:12:47.87,B2,SATODA,0000,0000,0000,,-Please help us out!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.00,0:12:49.79,B2,MIZUIRO,0000,0000,0000,,-So he’s done renting himself \Nout to the basketball team?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.32,0:12:52.32,B2,KEIGO,0000,0000,0000,,This sucks…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.32,0:12:54.75,B2,KEIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I won’t have Ichigo \Nto hang out with again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.35,0:12:58.71,B2,MIZUIRO,0000,0000,0000,,You make it sound like he \Nhangs with you all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.86,0:13:02.14,B2,KEIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Uh…that’s right, he does!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.14,0:13:03.44,B2,KEIGO,0000,0000,0000,,It’s not like I have nothing better
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.44,0:13:05.69,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,to do than making a nuisance of myself
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.69,0:13:07.56,B2,KEIGO,0000,0000,0000,,by bugging Ichigo at his \Npart time jobs all the time!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.56,0:13:09.56,B2,KEIGO,0000,0000,0000,,-It’s true, it’s true, \Nit’s so true, I swear!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.10,0:13:09.28,B2,MIZUIRO,0000,0000,0000,,-If you say so.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.28,0:13:10.78,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,-What’s my position?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.78,0:13:13.08,B2,SATODA,0000,0000,0000,,We’d like you to be our goalkeeper!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.08,0:13:14.73,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Chad would make a better goalkeeper.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.30,0:13:19.66,B2,SATODA,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Sado turned us down saying \Nhe found a better-paying job!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.66,0:13:20.43,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,So I’m his follow up?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.43,0:13:24.34,B2,KEIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Was Ichigo always so \Nobsessed with money?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.34,0:13:26.64,B2,MIZUIRO,0000,0000,0000,,He’s probably saving \Nup for after he graduates
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.08,0:13:29.05,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,so he can live on his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.05,0:13:30.15,B2,KEIGO,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.15,0:13:31.72,B2,KEIGO,0000,0000,0000,,You mean he’s moving out?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.97,0:13:34.71,B2,MIZUIRO,0000,0000,0000,,No, that I don’t know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.89,0:13:37.35,B2,MIZUIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever the case,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.81,0:13:40.73,B2,MIZUIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo’s old man \Ndoesn’t seem like the type
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.73,0:13:42.69,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,who’d loan Ichigo money for anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.62,0:13:46.93,B2,MIZUIRO,0000,0000,0000,,so I think it’s a good idea \Nfor him to save up now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.30,0:13:48.49,B2,KEIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.49,0:13:50.60,B2,KEIGO,0000,0000,0000,,You might be right about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.60,0:13:52.10,B2,SATODA,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.10,0:13:53.10,B2,SOCCER TEAM MEMBER B,0000,0000,0000,,We did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.10,0:13:55.23,B2,SOCCER TEAM MEMBER C,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Let’s go tell our captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.32,0:13:58.20,B2,KEIGO,0000,0000,0000,,You decided on the soccer team?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.20,0:13:59.60,B2,KEIGO,0000,0000,0000,,For how much?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.60,0:14:00.91,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,That’s a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.91,0:14:01.94,B2,MIZUIRO,0000,0000,0000,,When do you start?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.71,0:14:03.94,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Today.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.49,0:14:11.24,B2,TATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.07,0:14:13.77,B2,TATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to basketball?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.77,0:14:15.66,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,My contract ended last week.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.75,0:14:18.54,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,What about you? No after-school sports?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.90,0:14:20.22,B2,TATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I have my part-time job to go to.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.55,0:14:21.86,B2,TATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Didn’t I tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.32,0:14:25.09,B2,TATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Since last month, I’ve been \Nassistant instructor at my dojo.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.31,0:14:28.29,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,You’re the assistant instructor?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.78,0:14:30.72,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I’m glad I quit your dojo.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.63,0:14:34.48,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I refuse to call you Sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.48,0:14:38.02,B2,TATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Shall I force you to \Ncall me that right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.91,0:14:46.45,B2,MALE STUDENT A,0000,0000,0000,,It’s Miss Inoue…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.76,0:14:48.27,B2,MALE STUDENT B,0000,0000,0000,,She’s gorgeous…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.27,0:14:49.95,B2,MALE STUDENT B,0000,0000,0000,,Like an idol…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.62,0:14:52.40,B2,MALE STUDENT B,0000,0000,0000,,The first time I saw her, I thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.40,0:14:54.91,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,“Man, am I glad I came \Nto this high school!”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.32,0:14:58.18,B2,MALE STUDENT C,0000,0000,0000,,I took a picture of her the \Nother day with my cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.18,0:14:59.75,B2,MALE STUDENT A,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Send it to me!!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.72,0:15:01.63,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.88,0:15:05.21,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Kurosaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.21,0:15:06.76,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Tatsuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.51,0:15:08.97,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Inoue…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.39,0:15:12.86,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Stupid! That’s dangerous! \NYou’ll fall!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.86,0:15:14.18,B2,TATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,We can see your panties!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.26,0:15:16.60,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.60,0:15:18.21,B2,TATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,You deserved it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.21,0:15:19.91,B2,TATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,The next time you do \Nsomething that dangerous,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.91,0:15:22.15,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,I’ll hit you even harder!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.15,0:15:24.25,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Harder than just now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.25,0:15:25.86,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,You’ll crack open my head!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.41,0:15:29.19,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,You don’t have to \Nget so angry about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.19,0:15:30.61,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,She didn’t hurt herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.61,0:15:31.91,B2,TATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.91,0:15:33.90,B2,TATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,You have no business lecturing me
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.90,0:15:35.83,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,about how to teach Orihime a lesson!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.32,0:15:38.10,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I didn’t lecture you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.10,0:15:40.42,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I’m saying I feel sorry for Inoue!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.42,0:15:42.89,B2,TATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,That’s what I call lecturing!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.89,0:15:44.82,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Uh…the thing is…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.82,0:15:48.85,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,I want to ask the two \Nof you for your advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.24,0:15:50.26,B2,ICHIGO/TATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Advice?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.65,0:15:53.60,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It's about…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.38,0:15:58.36,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,my life’s theme, \N“The Hahaha Song,”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.36,0:16:02.01,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,where I cheer on comedians who have \Nthe right amount of popularity
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.01,0:16:05.98,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,by matching them to the tune \Nof the Do-Re-Mi song…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.52,0:16:08.54,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,“Right amount of \Npopularity”? What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.54,0:16:12.06,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,The problem is, recently, all \NI’m able to do is hum it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.06,0:16:14.07,B2,TATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Isn’t that a good thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.07,0:16:15.78,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you think that’s so?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.78,0:16:17.45,B2,TATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,You’ve grown up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.45,0:16:19.42,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.51,0:16:22.29,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,How do you do that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.58,0:16:24.38,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Your eyes look like the number 3!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.67,0:16:27.67,B2,TATSUKI (M),0000,0000,0000,,Orihime’s gotten a lot \Nbetter at making faces…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.02,0:16:29.03,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,The correct answer is!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.48,0:16:31.82,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Because I don’t know whether I should
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.82,0:16:35.26,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,start at “Do” with \NDokurodan or Doburock!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.26,0:16:36.73,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Which do you think would be better?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.73,0:16:37.81,B2,ICHIGO/TATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn’t matter!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.99,0:16:39.47,B2,TATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! I just remembered!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.47,0:16:41.13,B2,TATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I don’t have time for this!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.13,0:16:42.75,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,What’s the matter, Tatsuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.75,0:16:43.81,B2,TATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,My part-time job!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.81,0:16:45.25,B2,TATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Weren’t you working, too, Orihime?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.25,0:16:46.32,B2,TATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,You’d better get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.63,0:16:49.24,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,You sure are busy. Hang in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.24,0:16:52.25,B2,TATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,You act like none of this concerns you,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.25,0:16:54.41,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,but did you let your boss know?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.71,0:17:00.16,B2,TATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Didn’t your boss chew you \Nout for not doing that before?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.76,0:17:02.51,B2,TATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,If you don’t give her proper notice,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.51,0:17:04.67,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,don’t say I didn’t warn you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.89,0:17:06.90,B2,SATODA,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Kurosaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.56,0:17:09.59,B2,SATODA,0000,0000,0000,,Please join us at practice!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.97,0:17:11.51,B2,SATODA,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Kurosaki…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.51,0:17:12.34,B2,SATODA,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.56,0:17:13.76,B2,UNAGIYA,0000,0000,0000,,You dumb ass!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.60,0:17:18.76,B2,UNAGIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Do you realize what you’re asking?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.09,0:17:20.56,B2,UNAGIYA,0000,0000,0000,,You took off last week,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.56,0:17:22.80,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,and came to work only \None day after that,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.80,0:17:25.18,B2,UNAGIYA,0000,0000,0000,,and now you want to take \Noff another week again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.18,0:17:28.46,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,That’s why I’m apologizing…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.46,0:17:31.37,B2,UNAGIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think an apology \Nmakes it all okay?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.37,0:17:32.96,B2,UNAGIYA,0000,0000,0000,,You couldn’t care less, could you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.96,0:17:35.31,B2,UNAGIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Just get over here or you’re fired!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.46,0:17:40.59,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I am? All right, I \Nguess I had it coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.17,0:17:42.98,B2,UNAGIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.25,0:17:48.65,B2,UNAGIYA,0000,0000,0000,,N-No, hold on…what’re \Nyou saying, Ichigo my boy…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.65,0:17:50.72,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I’m saying I can’t \Nblame you for firing a guy
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.72,0:17:53.21,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,like me who doesn’t \Ntake his job seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.91,0:17:55.51,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I’m very sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.92,0:17:57.98,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for looking after \Nme for such a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.98,0:17:59.65,B2,UNAGIYA,0000,0000,0000,,It hasn’t been long!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.65,0:18:01.24,B2,UNAGIYA,0000,0000,0000,,It’s been only half a year!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.24,0:18:04.64,B2,UNAGIYA,0000,0000,0000,,The real fun of the Odd Jobs \NService is still ahead!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.08,0:18:07.58,B2,UNAGIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Our adventures will go on \Nfor a long time to come…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.63,0:18:11.39,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,And so the adventure ends…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.04,0:18:20.57,B2,OBUTA,0000,0000,0000,,There’s a guy named Kurosaki here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.86,0:18:22.56,B2,OBUTA,0000,0000,0000,,Come on out!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.31,0:18:25.60,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.60,0:18:27.50,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,What era is he from?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.79,0:18:30.30,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I don’t know any throwbacks \Nfrom another time like him…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.30,0:18:34.42,B2,OBUTA,0000,0000,0000,,He broke seven teeth of one of my boys!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.42,0:18:36.63,B2,OBUTA,0000,0000,0000,,Seven! Are you some kind of moron?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.01,0:18:39.01,B2,OBUTA,0000,0000,0000,,Normally it’s two at most!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.99,0:18:45.33,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh…that makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.58,0:18:48.62,B2,OBUTA,0000,0000,0000,,Kurosaki, I know you’re listening!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.62,0:18:50.83,B2,OBUTA,0000,0000,0000,,You’re probably trembling in fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.83,0:18:53.15,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,wondering how I found out your name!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.69,0:18:55.28,B2,OBUTA,0000,0000,0000,,You got careless!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.69,0:18:58.50,B2,OBUTA,0000,0000,0000,,He got a good look at your face!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.50,0:19:01.16,B2,OBUTA,0000,0000,0000,,I have ways of finding you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.77,0:19:03.57,B2,OBUTA,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, Kurosaki,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.82,0:19:05.56,B2,OBUTA,0000,0000,0000,,Until you come out,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.56,0:19:09.08,B2,OBUTA,0000,0000,0000,,me and my boys from Miyasho High \Nare sealing off the school gate!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.64,0:19:10.78,B2,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,You people…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.84,0:19:14.11,B2,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,Enough with the outdated antics.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.11,0:19:16.46,B2,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,Can’t you see you’re \Nmaking trouble for everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.22,0:19:21.74,B2,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, you guys seem on the smart \Nside for Kurosaki’s friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.05,0:19:24.47,B2,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,You understand what I’m saying, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.81,0:19:27.33,B2,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,Now hurry up and go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.33,0:19:28.98,B2,DELINQUENT A,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?! What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.30,0:19:30.94,B2,DELINQUENT A,0000,0000,0000,,Are you Kurosaki?
